
[1]phantasm

   PHAN'TASM, n. [Gr. to show, to shine, to appear.]

   That which appears to the mind; the image of an external object; hence,
   an idea or notion. It usually denotes a vain or airy appearance;
   something imagined.

   All the interim is

   Like a phantasm or a hideous dream.
